{"word":"G2766 - κέραμος - kéramos - ker'-am-os - Tiling","slug":"G2766","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">κέραμος</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>kéramos"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>ker'-am-os"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Tiling"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03BA;&#x03B5;&#x0301;&#x03C1;&#x03B1;&#x03BC;&#x03BF;&#x03C2; - keramos</b> - <i>ker'-am-os</i><p/>Probably from the base of <a href=\"#/G2767\">G2767</a> (through the idea of <i>mixing</i> clay and water); <i>earthenware</i>, that is, a <i>tile</i> (by analogy a thin <i>roof</i> or <i>awning</i>): - tiling."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G2763\">G2763</a>, <a href=\"#/G2764\">G2764</a>, <a href=\"#/G2765\">G2765</a>"}]}